text: The Health Service Executive (Irish: Feidhmeannacht na Seirbhíse Sláinte) is the publicly funded healthcare system in Ireland, responsible for health and personal social services. It started on 1 January 2005. The Minister for Health is responsible for it. In 2017 there were 67,145 workers and a budget of €16.05 billion. == References == Category:Medical and health organizations in the Republic of Ireland
title: Health Service Executive
